                        <msContents>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1ra" to="98rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of time</title>
                                <incipit defective="true">Per huius domine operationem mysterii</incipit>
                                <explicit>In resurrectione tua christe alleluya Celum et terra letentur</explicit>
                                <note>Several leaves missing in the beginning. The Proper of time begins with the Sunday after Nativity and the Office of St Sylvester. On <locus from="96vb" to="96vb" scheme="folios"/>: the lesson for Good Friday <quote>In tribulacione sua mane consurgent ad me</quote> (Hos. 6:1); on <locus from="97ra" to="97ra" scheme="folios"/>: part of the Resurrection Sunday antiphon <quote>Vidi aliquam egredientem de templo</quote> (<bibl>
                                        <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/101545">CAO </title>
                                        <citedRange from="5403" to="5403" unit="number"/>
                                    </bibl>); the feasts in between missing due to lost leaves. The first part of the Proper of time ends on <locus from="98rb" to="98rb" scheme="folios"/> with the Resurrection Sunday antiphon <quote>Sedit angelus</quote> (<bibl>
                                        <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/101545">CAO</title>
                                        <citedRange from="4858" to="4858" unit="number"/>
                                    </bibl>), and continues after the Ordo and Canon missae.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="98rb" to="105ra" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Ordo and Canon missae</title>
                                <rubric>Dicto offertorio et calice preparato sacerdos stans in medio altaris et dicat</rubric>
                                <incipit>Ueni sanctificator omnipotens inuisibilis deus</incipit>
                                <explicit>sit te miserante propiciabile in vitam eternam Amen</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> The Canon begins on <locus from="102ra" to="102ra" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                                    <p> Additions on <locus from="105ra" to="105vb" scheme="folios"/>: excerpts from Psalms and the prayer ‘Deus qui tribus pueris’ (<locus from="105ra" to="105ra" scheme="folios"/>), followed by the votive mass ‘Missa de quinque vulneribus Iesu Christi’, ed. <bibl>
                                            <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107361">Grüninger</title>
                                        </bibl> (1488); see <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107349">Kleberg (1974)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="131" to="131" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="106ra" to="166ra" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of time (continued)</title>
                                <incipit>Resurrexi et adhuc tecum sum (Ps. 138:18)</incipit>
                                <explicit>in nostra mente uitiosum est tue ipsius meditationis curetur Per dominum</explicit>
                                <note> The Proper of time begins with the Resurrection Sunday introitus and ends with the twenty-fifth Sunday after Pentecost.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="166rb" to="167vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Dedication of the church</title>
                                <rubric>In dedicatione ecclesie ad missam officium</rubric>
                                <incipit>Terribilis est locus iste</incipit>
                                <explicit>Qui viuis et regnas cum domino patre in vnitate spiritus sancti deus</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="168ra" to="175vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of saints</title>
                                <rubric>Sancti siluestri episcopi et confessoris collecta</rubric>
                                <incipit>Sacerdotes tui domine</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="true">Ego sum uitis vera participacione numeris</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> The Proper of saints begins with St Sylvester (31 December) and ends with St Vitalis (28 April, incomplete). A leaf missing after <locus from="172v" to="172v" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                                    <p> Notable feasts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="168v" to="168v" scheme="folios"/>: St Vincent the martyr (22 Jan.) </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="172rb" to="172rb" scheme="folios"/>: St Scholastica (10 Feb.) </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="172vb" to="172vb" scheme="folios"/>: St Juliana the martyr (16 Feb.) </p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
                        <physDesc>
                            <objectDesc>
                                <supportDesc material="parchment">
                                    <support>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="1r" to="175v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <material>Parchment</material>
                                            <dimensions type="leaf">
                                                <height quantity="295" unit="mm"/>
                                                <width quantity="195" unit="mm"/>
                                            </dimensions>
                                        </p>
                                    </support>
                                    <extent>
                                        <measure type="textblockLeaves" quantity="175" unit="folios"/>
                                    </extent>
                                    <condition>Several leaves missing at the beginning and end of the codex. <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: Half of the leaf missing. Leaves missing after <locus from="96v" to="96v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="105v" to="105v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="126v" to="126v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="172v" to="172v" scheme="folios"/>. Repairs on <locus from="8r" to="8r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="51r" to="51r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="54r" to="54r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="62r" to="62r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="68r" to="68r" scheme="folios"/>. Holes in the parchment throughout the volume, as well as smaller holes caused by insects. Several leaves torn, stained and dirty. Dried plant material has been placed in the gutters between <locus from="38v" to="38v" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="39r" to="39r" scheme="folios"/>; <locus from="58v" to="58v" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="59r" to="59r" scheme="folios"/>. Musical notes and text erased on <locus from="14r" to="14r" scheme="folios"/>.</condition>
                                </supportDesc>
                                <layoutDesc>
                                    <layout columns="2" ruledLines="33">
                                        <dimensions type="written">
                                            <height unit="mm" max="210" min="210"/>
                                            <width unit="mm" max="140" min="140"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                        <note>Guidelines and ruling in brown ink. Prickings in the margins.</note>
                                    </layout>
                                </layoutDesc>
                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">Textualis formata.</handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Bottom of page, in brown ink by an early modern hand: <quote>Lectiones et Cantiones annuae diebus Dominicalibus et festis per totum annum.</quote>
                                    </note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="15r" to="25r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>In the margin, in brown ink by a contemporary hand: references to the main text, especially Bible books.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="104v" to="104v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page, in brown ink by a contemporary hand: <quote>Domine sancte pater omnipotens eterne deus Da mihi hoc corpus quod sanguinem vnigeniti filii tui domini Dei nostri ita sumere vt merear per hoc remissionem omnium peccatorum meorum accipere et tuo sancto spiritu repleri quia tu es Deus et preter te non est alius cuius regnum gloriosum permanet in secula seculorum Amen</quote>. Bottom of page, in brown ink by a contemporary hand: a liturgical text added in textualis, partially illegible.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="105ra" to="105vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>In brown ink by two contemporary hands: excerpts from Psalms and a votive mass (see Contents above).</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="105vb" to="105vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Inventory from Husaby-Ernavi (later Husby-Långhundra) church in Uppland; see <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107349">Kleberg (1974)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="132" to="133" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>; <bibl>
                                            <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107125">SDHK</title>
                                            <citedRange from="19970" to="19970" unit="number"/>
                                        </bibl>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="128v" to="135r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>In the right margin, in brown ink by a contemporary hand: references to Bible books. On <locus from="132v" to="132v" scheme="folios"/> an illegible reference due to text loss.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="165r" to="165r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>In the right margin, in black ink by a contemporary hand: the number <quote>xxiii </quote>corrected to <quote>xxiiii</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="170v" to="170v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Bottom of page, in dark brown ink by a contemporary hand: text and musical notation for <quote>Sicut audiuimus et vidimus in ciuitate dei nostri in monte sancto eius</quote> (the Alleluia verse for the Feast of the Purification of the Virgin).</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <musicNotation>
                                <p>Four lines per stave, square notation. <locus from="133r" to="133r" scheme="folios"/>: Empty staves.</p>
                            </musicNotation>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink. Rubrics in red. Capitals touched in red. Roman numerals in red ink in the margins as well as in the main text.</p>
                                <decoNote type="images">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="101va" to="101va" scheme="folios"/> Canon miniature drawn in brown ink: Crucified Christ with eyes closed, Mary and John at either side of the cross; in the corners, symbols of Evangelists holding banderoles without text.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="100va" to="100va" scheme="folios"/>, <quote>P</quote>, <locus from="102ra" to="102ra" scheme="folios"/>, <quote>T</quote>, <locus from="106ra" to="106ra" scheme="folios"/>, <quote>R</quote>, <locus from="166rb" to="166rb" scheme="folios"/>, <quote>P</quote>: Puzzle initials in red and blue over 6-12 lines with extensions in the margin. Flourished initials in red and blue ink over 2-4 lines throughout the volume. Plain initials in brown and red ink over 3-4 lines in the musical notation. Plain initials in red and blue over 1 line throughout the volume.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="bookmarks">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="18r" to="18r" scheme="folios"/>: Bookmark in leather. <locus from="26r" to="26r" scheme="folios"/>:Trace of bookmark in leather with a blue thread.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
                        </physDesc>
